#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:3
#: d8cc96121cc14e34a3d0d9019d63200a
msgid "Installation troubleshooting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:7
#: 469fc6cd7dd4498193f9d1349ab6e45e
msgid "\"An unknown error has occurred\" error during installation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:10
#: d94b5f7ea5bc47678d37c3f8943b238a
msgid ""
"Some people have encountered this error message when trying to install "
"Qubes on drives that already have data on them. The solution is to exit "
"the installer, wipe all data or delete all partitions, then restart the "
"Qubes installation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:13
#: b9bf44fd49a549a3af281c9defca2a73
msgid "Trouble installing from USB stick"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:16
#: dcc9b7c693a14e0ea57085da54c7530f
msgid ""
"If you are facing issues when booting using UEFI mode, see the :doc:`UEFI"
" troubleshooting guide </user/troubleshooting/uefi-troubleshooting>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:18
#: a590de0ffd3143029eb16eec7fb5c3b0
msgid ""
"There are a variety of other problems that could arise when using a USB "
"installation medium, and some of the issues can be fixed by doing one or "
"more of the following:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:20
#: 0088729f83cf4440b23059de502e5e65
msgid ""
"**Use a different USB drive:** If possible, try several drives of "
"different sizes and formats. This determines whether the problem stems "
"from the flash drive or Qubes installer. Some laptops cannot read from an"
" external boot device larger than 8GB. If you encounter a black screen "
"when performing an installation from a USB stick, ensure you are using a "
"USB drive less than 8GB, or a partition on that USB less than 8GB and of "
"format FAT32. Note that the Qubes installation image is over 4GB, so it "
"may not fit on a smaller USB. If a machine can not boot from a bigger "
"USB, it may be too old to run Qubes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:22
#: 573ed5f250e542f2b1571ff9f88956d3
msgid ""
"**Verify your Qubes ISO:** Errors will occur if the Qubes installer is "
"corrupted. Ensure that the installer is correct and complete before "
"writing it to a flash drive by :doc:`verifying the ISO </project-security"
"/verifying-signatures>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:24
#: 6dbbec2828f14777845776c2e352b089
msgid ""
"**Change the method you used to** :ref:`write your ISO to a USB key <user"
"/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide:copying the iso onto"
" the installation medium>` **:** Some people use the ``dd`` command "
"(recommended), others use tools like Rufus, balenaEtcher or the GNOME "
"Disk Utility. If installation fails after using one tool, try a different"
" one. For example, if you are facing trouble installing Qubes after "
"writing the ISO using Rufus, then try using other tools like balenaEtcher"
" or the ``dd`` command. In case the boot partition is not set to “active”"
" after copying the ISO, you can use some other tool like ``gparted`` on a"
" Linux system to activate it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:29
#: 4993740b80ec488596e5ae289d3f368a
msgid ""
"\"**Warning:** dracut-initqueue timeout - starting timeout scripts\" "
"during installation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:32
#: c8b3763dc7044330891767bf8540ae80
msgid ""
"This error message is related to the faulty creation of the USB "
"installation medium. If you receive this error message during "
"installation, please make sure you have followed the instructions on "
":ref:`how to write your ISO to a USB key <user/downloading-installing-"
"upgrading/installation-guide:copying the iso onto the installation "
"medium>`. Specifically, the ``dd`` command listed on that page has been "
"verified to solve this issue on multiple Qubes installation versions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:40
#: f0a0d71bc90447fc94263cc0ea6e11bc
msgid ""
"See `here <https://github.com/QubesOS/qubes-issues/issues/6447>`__ for a "
"discussion of this error message."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:43
#: 569ffed25faf46c1a9e56c925e623fa9
msgid ""
"Boot screen does not appear / system does not detect your installation "
"medium"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:46
#: 069630e188c641219f60a1a40393c96b
msgid ""
"If the boot screen does not appear, there are several options to "
"troubleshoot. First, try rebooting your computer. If it still loads your "
"currently installed operating system or does not detect your installation"
" medium, make sure the boot order is set up appropriately."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:48
#: ad4f808d68b74994ac261e92c37339bf
msgid ""
"The process to change the boot order varies depending on the currently "
"installed system and the motherboard manufacturer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:50
#: 77a25af8de154617974f794191602248
msgid ""
"If **Windows 10** is installed on your machine, you may need to follow "
"specific instructions to change the boot order. This may require an "
"`advanced reboot <https://support.microsoft.com/en-"
"us/help/4026206/windows-10-find-safe-mode-and-other-startup-settings>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:53
#: 747ae7bf90dc4577914f9ce54d08cfd9
msgid ""
"\"Not asking for VNC because we don't have a network\" / \"X startup "
"failed, aborting installation\" / \"Pane is dead\" error during "
"installation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:56
#: 96a337b24d394ab18dae6df7e9eb7b04
msgid ""
"The boot mode in use may be causing these error messages. Try to install "
"after enabling both UEFI and legacy boot modes. If that doesn’t help, "
"then disable one and try the other. Visit the :doc:`UEFI Troubleshooting "
"guide </user/troubleshooting/uefi-troubleshooting>` if other errors arise"
" during UEFI booting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:58
#: ded962de1555401d8b901a0366c4f28a
msgid ""
"These errors may also occur due to an incompatible Nvidia graphics card. "
"If you have one, follow the following instructions:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:60
#: fc336949b5c0420cb3cd9e461ff0f199
msgid "Disable secure/fast boot and use legacy mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:62
#: 099a5de009414fc98b7eeabf9d56e7fa
msgid ""
"Enter GRUB, move the selection to the first choice, and then press the "
"Tab key."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:64
#: e2efc3f1aaff448a838def679f7cbd25
msgid ""
"Now, you are in edit mode. Move the text cursor with your arrow key and "
"after ``kernel=`` line, add:"
msgstr ""

