#: 893f12cd24ec47baa87d221493a103ce
msgid "If the above code doesn’t fix the problem, replace it with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:80
#: 58807641694b498f92bbdcc87d24c620
msgid ""
"For more information, look at the `Nvidia Troubleshooting guide "
"<https://forum.qubes-os.org/t/19021#disabling-nouveau>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:83
#: bf09b48d1acc4e2f8a984767445d006c
msgid "Installation freezes at \"Setting up Networking\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:86
#: cb5d6e8189df4c86b182a20a371a7691
msgid ""
"If you are facing this problem on an Apple computer, check out the "
"`Macbook Troubleshooting guide <https://forum.qubes-os.org/t/19020>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:88
#: 3c1f431c4ead4a39ba348a8da1b90b18
msgid ""
"If you are installing Qubes 4.0 on an external storage device, you may "
"have forgotten to disable ``sys-usb`` during the :ref:`initial setup "
"<user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide:initial "
"setup>`, which is generally required for that setup to work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:90
#: d90d3f4f58ec446f94463ce0f394a314
msgid ""
"This issue occurs due to the network card, which may be missing some "
"drivers or is incompatible with Qubes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:92
#: 83961c9207314f7cba57f27ba437f838
msgid ""
"First, install all available drivers for the card. You can install the "
"drivers without internet access by first downloading them on another "
"machine, then transferring them over to the current machine (e.g., with a"
" USB drive)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:94
#: 304d51bd2b754a2ebe54fea377279db8
msgid ""
"If installing the available drivers does not help, disable the network "
"card in the BIOS and perform the installation before re-enabling the "
"card. If this solves the issue, it confirms the PCI card is incompatible "
"with Qubes. In this case, you may want to consider replacing it with a "
"network card of a different brand. Broadcom cards are notoriously "
"problematic with Qubes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:97
#: db89c825949f405aa9fc0db572ffb9fc
msgid "\"Unsupported Hardware Detected\" error"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:100
#: dd863e506f974fb5a0e8253412f8b083
msgid ""
"During Qubes installation, you may come across the error message which "
"reads “Unsupported Hardware Detected. Missing features: IOMMU/VT-d/AMD-"
"Vi, Interrupt Remapping. Without these features, Qubes OS will not "
"function normally”."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:102
#: ea65e1e800294f659d7526ddf1ba309c
msgid ""
"This error message indicates that IOMMU-virtualization hasn’t been "
"activated in the BIOS. Return to the :ref:`hardware requirements <user"
"/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide:hardware "
"requirements>` section to learn how to activate it. If the setting is not"
" configured correctly, it means that your hardware won’t be able to "
"leverage some Qubes security features, such as a strict isolation of the "
"networking and USB hardware."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:104
#: c0fe9e04d13143b4acb6d70b4e1f148b
msgid ""
"In Qubes 4.0, the default installation won’t function properly without "
"IOMMU, as default sys-net and sys-usb qubes require IOMMU. It is possible"
" to configure them to reduce isolation and not use IOMMU by changing "
"virtualization mode of these two VMs to “PV”."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:106
#: d9de53742b864d4eaeeee9af8d03101e
msgid ""
"In Qubes 4.1, the default sys-net and sys-usb qubes need additional "
"configuration to be usable without an IOMMU. Otherwise they will fail to "
"start with this error message:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:114
#: 6f1d6c757bd040469ddeb2f295ca5566
msgid ""
"To confirm that a missing IOMMU is causing this problem, check for the "
"following error message in ``/var/log/libvirt/libxl/libxl-driver.log``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:122
#: cf60d3a38f2a43f09d52243b73383727
msgid ""
"Here are the steps to fix this. Note that this allows sys-net and sys-usb"
" to take complete control of the system, as described in the :ref:`FAQ "
"here <introduction/faq:why is vt-d\\/amd-vi\\/amd iommu important?>`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:124
#: ae807adddda14769b971ee688973476e
msgid "Change the virtualization mode of sys-net and sys-usb to “PV”"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:126
#: ed1c6b4a18424eb1a5ab2c51d9993e43
msgid ""
"Add ``qubes.enable_insecure_pv_passthrough`` to ``GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX`` in"
" ``/etc/default/grub``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:128
#: bf41e79c0f574785a6dc4f4fffc7fc7f
msgid ""
"Run ``sudo grub2-mkconfig -o /boot/efi/EFI/qubes/grub.cfg``. If you are "
"using a non-UEFI BIOS (where ``/boot/efi/EFI`` doesn’t exist), use the "
"command ``sudo grub-mkconfig -o /boot/grub2/grub.cfg`` instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/installation-troubleshooting.rst:130
#: fa13391c1bf143a299ad07055b3d4c0c
msgid "Reboot"
msgstr ""

